verses.text_plain: Behold, thou art fair, my love; behold, thou art fair; thou hast doves’ eyes within thy locks: thy hair is as a flock of goats, that appear from mount Gilead.
verses.verse_html:
1Behold, thou art fair, my love; behold, thou art fair; thou hast doves’ eyes within thy locks: thy hair is as a flock of goats, that appear from mount Gilead. ▼
▼ that…: or, that eat of, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that…: or, that eat of, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: or, that eat of, etc

verses.text_plain: Thy teeth are like a flock of sheep that are even shorn, which came up from the washing; whereof every one bear twins, and none is barren among them.
verses.verse_html: 2Thy teeth are like a flock of sheep that are even shorn, which came up from the washing; whereof every one bear twins, and none is barren among them.

verses.text_plain: Thy lips are like a thread of scarlet, and thy speech is comely: thy temples are like a piece of a pomegranate within thy locks.
verses.verse_html: 3Thy lips are like a thread of scarlet, and thy speech is comely: thy temples are like a piece of a pomegranate within thy locks.

verses.text_plain: Thy neck is like the tower of David builded for an armoury, whereon there hang a thousand bucklers, all shields of mighty men.
verses.verse_html: 4Thy neck is like the tower of David builded for an armoury, whereon there hang a thousand bucklers, all shields of mighty men.

verses.text_plain: Thy two breasts are like two young roes that are twins, which feed among the lilies.
verses.verse_html: 5Thy two breasts are like two young roes that are twins, which feed among the lilies.

verses.text_plain: Until the day break, and the shadows flee away, I will get me to the mountain of myrrh, and to the hill of frankincense.
verses.verse_html:
6Until the day break, and the shadows flee away, I will get me to the mountain of myrrh, and to the hill of frankincense. ▼
▼ break: Heb. breathe

verses.text_plain: Thou art all fair, my love; there is no spot in thee.
verses.verse_html: 7Thou art all fair, my love; there is no spot in thee.

verses.text_plain: Come with me from Lebanon, my spouse, with me from Lebanon: look from the top of Amana, from the top of Shenir and Hermon, from the lions’ dens, from the mountains of the leopards.
verses.verse_html: 8Come with me from Lebanon, my spouse, with me from Lebanon: look from the top of Amana, from the top of Shenir and Hermon, from the lions’ dens, from the mountains of the leopards.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast ravished my heart, my sister, my spouse; thou hast ravished my heart with one of thine eyes, with one chain of thy neck.
verses.verse_html:
9Thou hast ravished my heart, my sister, my spouse; thou hast ravished my heart with one of thine eyes, with one chain of thy neck. ▼
▼ ravished: or, taken away

footnotes.body_html: ▼ ravished: or, taken away

verses.text_plain: How fair is thy love, my sister, my spouse! how much better is thy love than wine! and the smell of thine ointments than all spices!
verses.verse_html: 10How fair is thy love, my sister, my spouse! how much better is thy love than wine! and the smell of thine ointments than all spices!

verses.text_plain: Thy lips, O my spouse, drop as the honeycomb: honey and milk are under thy tongue; and the smell of thy garments is like the smell of Lebanon.
verses.verse_html: 11Thy lips, O my spouse, drop as the honeycomb: honey and milk are under thy tongue; and the smell of thy garments is like the smell of Lebanon.

verses.text_plain: A garden inclosed is my sister, my spouse; a spring shut up, a fountain sealed.
verses.verse_html:
12A garden inclosed is my sister, my spouse; a spring shut up, a fountain sealed. ▼
▼ inclosed: Heb. barred
 , ▼
▼ shut up: Heb. barred

footnotes.body_html: ▼ shut up: Heb. barred

verses.text_plain: Thy plants are an orchard of pomegranates, with pleasant fruits; camphire, with spikenard,
verses.verse_html:
13Thy plants are an orchard of pomegranates, with pleasant fruits; camphire, with spikenard, ▼
▼ camphire: or, cypress

verses.text_plain: Spikenard and saffron; calamus and cinnamon, with all trees of frankincense; myrrh and aloes, with all the chief spices:
verses.verse_html: 14Spikenard and saffron; calamus and cinnamon, with all trees of frankincense; myrrh and aloes, with all the chief spices:

verses.text_plain: A fountain of gardens, a well of living waters, and streams from Lebanon.
verses.verse_html: 15A fountain of gardens, a well of living waters, and streams from Lebanon.

verses.text_plain: Awake, O north wind; and come, thou south; blow upon my garden, that the spices thereof may flow out. Let my beloved come into his garden, and eat his pleasant fruits.
verses.verse_html: 16Awake, O north wind; and come, thou south; blow upon my garden, that the spices thereof may flow out. Let my beloved come into his garden, and eat his pleasant fruits.
